ity is considered instead of mass. Although\nthe dust continuum emission resolves clumps in a network of filaments, some of\nwhich consist of hub-filament systems, the majority of the MMCs are not found\nin the hubs. Our analysis shows that high-mass cores and MMCs have no preferred\nlocation with respect to low-mass cores at the earliest stages of high-mass\nstar formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Apr 2023 12:48:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-05"}
